From acd4b626e10fbbeb7867ec98f6a92688c5fa1806 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 27 Jul 2025 21:43:50 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 7/8] QSDK: CP: hostapd: ATF: Build ATF candidate list

Build ATF candidate list is the second step of algorithm.
Once timer expires,
	1. it will sort and map all the ssid to
respective groups.
	2. iterate all peer configs and check if station with that
mac is associated and mark it as configured. (this is explicit peer)
	3. iterate through all peers associated to radio and
put it to implicit or explicit list.

Here, implicit peers are the peers which is not configured by the
user but are associated in the radio. Explicit peers are the peers
which are configured by the user.

Based on the candidate list generated, the airtime distribution
takes place.

Signed-off-by: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
